pageContext.claim: “In the past two years, Customs and Border Protection seizures of meth and cocaine and heroin and fentanyl at the southern border are up 45 percent, and going up much higher.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump mixes and matches a bunch of different drugs to come up with this figure. Fentanyl seizures are up substantially, as is methamphetamine. But cocaine and heroin seizures are basically flat. Marijuana seizures are down substantially.
